U.K.’s Hague Tells Bahrain Minister of Serious Concern on Unrest

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-16T22:46:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/u-k-s-hague-tells-bahrain-minister-of-serious-concern-on-unrest.html
U.K. Foreign Secretary  William Hague  told Bahraini Foreign Minister Sheikh Khalid bin Ahmed Al-
Khalifa that the U.K. is “seriously concerned” about clashes
between protesters and security forces in Bahrain and called on
“all parties to engage in an open and constructive national
dialogue” leading to “tangible actions that respond to the
legitimate aspirations of the Bahraini people,” the Foreign and
Commonwealth Office said in an e-mailed statement this evening.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 